TY  - JOUR
TI  - Transitive Multi-Stage Majority Decisions with Quasi-Transitive Individual Preferences
AU  - Batra, Raveendra
AU  - Pattanaik, Prasanta K.
AB  - [Sufficient conditions (in terms of restrictions on individual preferences) have been already established in the literature for transitivity of simple majority decisions when individual preferences are quasi-transitive (but not necessarily transitive) and also for transitivity of multi-stage majority decisions when individual preferences are transitive. This paper establishes sufficient conditions for transitivity of multi-stage majority decisions when individual preferences are quasi-transitive, but not necessarily transitive. This constitutes a generalization of several results proved earlier.]
C1  - Full publication date: Nov., 1972
